ard as D3-T4.1 follow-up).\n26\t- [ ] Regenerate `.gsd-t/token-log.md` from backfilled JSONL — **BLOCKED** on T4.1 (verified empirically: regenerating against the current 2-row JSONL would truncate the 434-line hand-maintained log; `git checkout HEAD` restored).\n27\t\n28\t### D3-T5 — Tests — **DONE** (2026-04-21, 9/9 pass)\n29\t- [x] `test/m43-schema-v2.test.js` — 9 tests: backward-compat, v2 pass-through, tool_attribution/compaction_pressure pass-through, empty-array omission, regenerate idempotence, deterministic sort, missing-usage `—`, empty JSONL header-only, v1-row backward compat.\n30\t- [x] Token cluster: 60/60. Full suite: 1569/1571 (2 pre-existing fails unrelated).\n31\t\n32\t### D3-T6 — Doc ripple — **DONE** (2026-04-21)\n33\t- [x] `docs/architecture.md`: added \"Token Pipeline (M40 → M41 → M43 D3)\" block under Context Observability.\n34\t- [x] `.gsd-t/progress.md` Decision Log: 2026-04-21 23:00 entry.\n35\t- [ ] `CLAUDE.md` Observability block: intentionally unchanged — wrapper signature additions are backward-compatible; existing Pattern A / Pattern B examples still correct.\n36\t\n37\t## Follow-up (carried inside D3)\n38\t\n39\t### D3-T4.1 — Backfill parser extension\n40\t- Extend `bin/gsd-t-token-backfill.cjs` to recognize pre-aggregator headless-log shapes (human-readable Claude output without stream-json `result` frames).\n41\t- Re-run dry-run after extension; expect non-zero envelopes against the 42 historical files.\n42\t- Then complete D3-T4 apply-path + regenerate.\n43\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"96e7dda7-b960-48d1-b1cb-90373ff412c9","uuid":"47ee271a-7baf-4329-8502-fc5a4b761974","timestamp":"2026-04-21T23:31:58.639Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/projects/GSD-T/.gsd-t/domains/m43-d3-sink-unification-backfill/tasks.md","content":"# Tasks: m43-d3-sink-unification-backfill\n\n## Wave 1 — Foundation (concurrent with D1)\n\n### D3-T1 — Author `metrics-schema-contract.md` v2 — **DONE** (2026-04-2