{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W85mt76FKaKZLhPZNqTXme","type":"tool_result","content":"75\t| M37 Universal Context Auto-Pause | 3.11.10 | 2026-04-16 | v3.11.10 | Strengthened context meter additionalContext from suggestion to MANDATORY STOP instruction; context-meter-contract v1.2.0; CLAUDE-global Universal Auto-Pause Rule section; Step 0.2 in 5 loop commands; 1228/1228 tests |\n76\t| M36 Cross-Platform Unattended Supervisor Loop | 3.10.10 | 2026-04-15 | v3.10.10 | Detached supervisor relay for 24h+ unattended milestone execution; 3 new slash commands (unattended/unattended-watch/unattended-stop); ScheduleWakeup(270s) in-session watch loop; /clear+/resume auto-reattach via Step 0; cross-platform (macOS/Linux/Windows except sleep-prevention); safety rails (gutter/blocker/timeout); 1226/1226 tests |\n77\t| M35 Runway-Protected Execution | 2.76.10 | 2026-04-15 | v2.76.10 | Removed silent quality degradation; surgical per-phase model selection; pre-flight runway estimator with headless auto-spawn; 18-field per-spawn token telemetry; detect-only optimization backlog; 985/985 tests |\n78\t| M34 Context Meter | 2.75.10 | 2026-04-14 | v2.75.10 | Real context-window measurement via Anthropic count_tokens API; replaces task-counter proxy entirely; 941/941 tests |\n79\t\n80\tOlder milestones (M33 and earlier) archived under `.gsd-t/milestones/` — see directory listing for the full index.\n81\t\n82\t## Blockers\n83\t<!-- No active blockers -->\n84\t\n85\t## Decision Log\n86\t\n87\t> Prior decision log entries preserved in `.gsd-t/milestones/*/progress.md` — see archive snapshots (most recently `M40-external-task-orchestrator-2026-04-20/progress.md`) for pre-M40 history.\n88\t\n89\t- 2026-04-21 23:55: [execute M43 · D1 Wave 1 · orphan-iter recovery] Branch B (transcript-sourced) in-session usage capture. Work was completed by an unattended worker that was SIGTERM'd mid-iteration during the 23:30 supervisor cleanup; recovered as a discrete commit since tests pass and the contract surface is sound. **`bin/gsd-t-in-session-usage.cjs`** (new) — exports `captureInSessionUsage({sessionId, transcriptPath, command, model, projectDir, sessionType, since})` and `processHookPayload({projectDir, payload})`. `captureInSessionUsage` reads the transcript JSONL at `transcriptPath`, scans for `assistant` lines with `message.usage`, generates one v2 row per turn (idempotent via `since` cursor on `message.id` / line offset), and writes through `recordSpawnRow` with `skipMarkdownLog: true` so per-turn rows land in `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` only — `token-log.md` stays the regenerated view (D3 contract). Returns `{rows, reason?}`. Reasons: `missing-session-or-transcript` (graceful no-op for hook fires without payload), `no-turns` (transcript exists but has no usage-bearing assistant lines yet), `ok` (rows emitted). **`scripts/hooks/gsd-t-in-session-usage-hook.js`** (new) — thin SessionEnd / Stop hook entry point that reads the JSON payload from stdin, derives `projectDir` from `cwd`, and calls `mod.processHookPayload({projectDir, payload})`. Hook is the wire-up artifact for D1-T1's Branch B decision; no settings.json edit yet (still gated on user permission). **`bin/gsd-t-token-capture.cjs`** — added `skipMarkdownLog` boolean option to `recordSpawnRow` (default false). High-frequency producers (D1 per-turn, D2 joiner) write JSONL only; the markdown table is regenerated via `gsd-t tokens --regenerate-log`. Backward compatible: existing callers omit the flag and the `.gsd-t/token-log.md` write happens as before. **`test/m43-in-session-usage.test.js`** (new, 290 lines, 10 tests, all pass): one-turn → one row, three-turn → three rows with distinct turn_id, replay over same transcript = zero new rows (idempotence), incremental append = exactly one new row, assistant lines without usage ignored + user lines skipped, missing transcript_path → `missing-session-or-transcript`, non-existent transcript path → `no-turns` (graceful), `null` usage writes a row with `hasUsage=false`, **multi-turn emission does NOT append to token-log.md (JSONL-only)**, real-probe-shape payload (session_id + transcript_path + cwd) processes without error. **`.gsd-t/domains/m43-d1-in-session-usage-capture/tasks.md`** — task statuses updated. Files touched this iter: 4 new + 2 modified = 5 (excluding the supervisor stream-json patch in `bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs`, which is held uncommitted intentionally per session direction). D1 cluster: 10/10 pass; full suite re-run not done in this commit (will be re-run by next supervisor iter). No contract changes (v2 schema accepts the rows as-is). No new API endpoints. CLAUDE.md/README.md unchanged. Next: relaunch unattended supervisor — D1 hook payload wire-up still needs settings.json permission to fire on Stop / SessionEnd; D2/D3-T4-followup/Wave 2 next in chain.\n90\t\n91\t- 2026-04-21 23:25: [bug-fix · supervisor] `isMilestoneComplete` rewritten to read STRUCTURED progress.md anchors (`## Status:` header phase keyword + Milestones-table row third column) instead of grep-the-prose. **Symptom**: M43 unattended supervisor exited `done` after iter 1 (2026-04-21 22:50→23:00, only D3 W1 + partition committed; D1/D2/D4/D5/D6 + W2/W3 untouched) because the old impl matched any line containing both `M43` and the word `complete(d)?`, and the live `progress.md` had three such lines (the new 23:15 Decision Log entry mentioning \"completed in this iter\", the M43 DEFINED scope text, and the M42 COMPLETE entry that ends \"Awaiting user direction for M43\"). **Fix** (`bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs:1485`): replaced two `body.split` regex grep loops with two structural matchers — (1) `^##\\s*Status:[^\\n]*\\bMxx\\b\\s+([A-Z][A-Z-]+)` reads the first ALL-CAPS phase keyword after the milestone id; (2) `^\\|\\s*Mxx\\s*\\|[^|]*\\|\\s*([A-Z][A-Z-]+)\\s*\\|` reads the third pipe-column of the Milestones table row. Phase is terminal iff in `{COMPLETE, COMPLETED, DONE, VERIFIED}`. Decision Log entries (always `- 2026-...`) and descriptive paragraphs no longer satisfy the check — both targets are structural anchors that complete-milestone explicitly maintains. Verified against live `progress.md`: M43=false (PARTITIONED), M42=true (table row COMPLETE), M41=true. **Test**: new `test/m43-milestone-complete-detection.test.js` (8 tests, all pass) — covers status-header positive, table-row positive, PARTITIONED non-terminal, the exact Decision Log false-positive that caused this incident, missing id, UNKNOWN id, missing file, alternate terminal phases (COMPLETED/DONE/VERIFIED), and a live-progress.md sanity assert. Full suite: **1580/1580 pass** (was 1572 → +8). Operational consequence: relaunching unattended with the fix in place means the supervisor will correctly chain D1 hook wire-up + D3-T4.1 backfill parser + Wave 2 + Wave 3 across many iterations until the Milestones table row for M43 actually flips to COMPLETE (which `complete-milestone` writes). Next: republish, version-update-all, relaunch unattended over M43.\n92\t\n93\t- 2026-04-21 23:15: [quick · M43-D6-pre] Live transcript tee — the M42 D1 post-hoc transcript write was replaced with a streaming path so `/transcript/:id/stream` renders worker output as it arrives instead of at worker exit. **`bin/gsd-t-unattended-platform.cjs`**: the async heartbeat spawn path now accepts `opts.onStdoutLine(line)`; the stdout `data` handler line-splits on `\\n`, invokes the callback per completed line, and flushes any trailing partial line on `close`. Callback errors are swallowed (best-effort tee). JSDoc updated. **`bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs`**: `_spawnWorker` now passes `onStdoutLine: (line) => transcriptTee.appendFrame({spawnId, projectDir, frame: line})` when a transcript has been allocated; the old post-hoc stdout-split block in `finalize()` is removed — `finalize` now only calls `closeTranscript` with the terminal status. **`test/unattended-platform.test.js`**: the import was repointed from the stale `.js` sibling to the live `.cjs` (fixes the test/prod divergence flagged by M39 red-team BUG-3); fake-supervisor shim updated to read argv[3] since spawnSupervisor prepends `\"unattended\"` subcommand; added 1 test asserting `onStdoutLine` fires per line as stdout streams and returns the same final stdout buffer. **`test/m42-unattended-tee.test.js`**: fake platform spawn now invokes `opts.onStdoutLine` per line (matches the new contract — post-hoc tee is gone). **`scripts/gsd-t-dashboard.html`**: port default `params.get('port')||'7433'` → `params.get('port')||location.port||'7433'` so SSE works on project-hashed ports (7455 here). **`test/dashboard-server.test.js`**: asserts the new port fallback. Full suite: **1572/1572 pass**. Caveat: this patch takes effect only for supervisors launched AFTER this commit — Node's module cache is per-process, so any already-running supervisor keeps executing the pre-patch code. Next: relaunch unattended after the version bump + publish so the running supervisor loads the live tee.\n94\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"96e7dda7-b960-48d1-b1cb-90373ff412c9","uuid":"5f0a21a3-c62c-4f79-8ae7-ee8c91afe474","timestamp":"2026-04-21T23:35:59.494Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/projects/GSD-T/.gsd-t/progress.md","content":"| M37 Universal Context Auto-Pause | 3.11.10 | 2026-04-16 | v3.11.10 | Strengthened context meter additionalContext from suggestion to MANDATORY STOP instruction; context-meter-contract v1.2.0; CLAUDE-global Universal Auto-Pause Rule section; Step 0.2 in 5 loop commands; 1228/1228 tests |\n| M36 Cross-Platform Unattended Supervisor Loop | 3.10.10 | 2026-04-15 | v3.10.10 | Detached supervisor relay for 24h+ unattended milestone execution; 3 new slash commands (unattended/unattended-watch/unattended-stop); ScheduleWakeup(270s) in-session watch loop; /clear+/resume auto-reattach via Step 0; cross-platform (macOS/Linux/Windows except sleep-prevention); safety rails (gutter/blocker/t