 surfaced a parser-gap finding. **D3-T2 wrapper pass-through**: `bin/gsd-t-token-capture.cjs` `SCHEMA_VERSION` bumped 1 → 2; `_buildJsonlRecord` + `recordSpawnRow` + `captureSpawn` now pass through optional v2 fields (`sessionId` → `session_id`, `turnId` → `turn_id`, `sessionType`, `toolAttribution` → `tool_attribution`, `compactionPressure` → `compaction_pressure`). Fields only emit when explicitly provided — existing callers unchanged (v1-shape call produces a row with `schemaVersion: 2` and no v2 fields present, which is a valid v2 row per contract §Backward compatibility). Empty `toolAttribution: []` is omitted rather than emitted as `[]` (keeps historical rows indistinguishable between \"no attribution available\" and \"attribution = nothing\"). **D3-T3 regenerate-log**: new `bin/gsd-t-token-regenerate-log.cjs` (~110 lines, zero deps, reuses `NEW_HEADER`/`NEW_SEP`/`_formatTokensCell` from the capture module); reads `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl`, sorts deterministically by `startedAt` asc → `session_id` asc → `turn_id` asc (numeric when both parse, lex otherwise), writes `.gsd-t/token-log.md`. Exports `regenerateLog`/`renderMarkdown`/`sortRows`. Registered as `gsd-t tokens --regenerate-log` in `bin/gsd-t.js` (help text updated). **D3-T5 tests**: `test/m43-schema-v2.test.js` — 9 tests, all pass: backward-compat (v1-caller yields v2 row minus new fields), v2 pass-through (session_id/turn_id/sessionType), tool_attribution + compaction_pressure pass-through, empty array omission, regenerate idempotence (byte-identical on repeated run), deterministic sort including numeric turn_id ordering (a/2 before a/10 before b/2), missing-usage → `—`, empty JSONL → header-only file, schemaVersion=1 rows render correctly. Two existing M41 assertions updated from `assert.equal(rec.schemaVersion, 1)` → `assert.equal(rec.schemaVersion, capture.SCHEMA_VERSION)` (v2 is additive — v1-shape callers keep working, just tagged with the current version number). **D3-T4 dry-run backfill