— zero code changed, no tests added/changed. M43 still DEFINED, not yet partitioned. Next: `/gsd-t-partition M43` to refresh the partition with the revised D4/D5/D6, then proceed `discuss → plan → execute`.\n\n- 2026-04-21 14:30: [quick] Multi-project isolation — (A) project-hashed dashboard default port (djb2 hash of resolved `projectDir` into `[7433, 7532]`, explicit `--port` wins; `projectScopedDefaultPort` + `resolvePort` helpers exported from `scripts/gsd-t-dashboard-server.js`; 8 unit tests in `test/dashboard-port-project-scope.test.js` covering determinism, range, and override precedence) and (B) supervisor.pid JSON fingerprint (`bin/supervisor-pid-fingerprint.cjs` new, ~120 lines: `writePidFile`/`readPidFile` emit/consume `{pid, projectDir, startedAt}` JSON with backward-compat read of legacy bare-integer form → `{form: \"legacy\"}`; `verifyFingerprint(entry, projectDir, {_execSync})` returns `ok:true|false|null` with reasons `project_mismatch`/`process_not_found`/`command_not_gsd_t`/`ps_failed`/`legacy_fingerprint` — ps command-line match via `/gsd-t|unattended/i` regex; `bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs` write site swapped from `fs.writeFileSync(pidPath, String(process.pid))` to `writePidFile(projectDir, process.pid)`; `commands/gsd-t-resume.md` Step 0 replaced bare `kill -0` with a five-outcome node -e call — `no_pid_file` / `dead:<pid>` / `alive_verified:<pid>` / `alive_legacy_pid:<pid>` / `alive_but_stale:<pid>:<reason>` — legacy entries log a one-line upgrade hint then behave like verified so already-running legacy supervisors aren't disturbed). Contract `unattended-supervisor-contract.md` v1.4.0 → v1.4.1 (§2 prose + §17 version history row; §8 in the prompt refers to PID file lifecycle which actually lives in §2 of this contract). 8 new PART B unit tests in `test/supervisor-pid-fingerprint.test.js`. **Currently-paused supervisor on disk was NOT disturbed** — no relaunch, state.json/stop/run logs untouched, new write format takes effect at next `gsd-t unattended` launch. Tests before this session: 1553/1553. Tests after: 1561/1561 (+8 from PART B fingerprint suite). PART A code (helper + wiring + 8-test file) was already on disk uncommitted at session start — committed together with PART B since both are the multi-project-isolation theme. **Currently-paused supervisor on disk was NOT disturbed** (state.json/stop/run.log untouched and excluded from this commit per directive).\n- 2026-04-21 13:50: [quick] Transcript SSE route — added `event: status` (waiting/empty) and `event: end` (finished spawn) semantics + 4 unit tests. `scripts/gsd-t-dashboard-server.js` `handleTranscriptStream` now: (1) on missing `.gsd-t/transcripts/{spawn-id}.ndjson` emits `event: status\\ndata:{\"status\":\"waiting\",...}` and holds the stream open with keepalive (no fs.watchFile since the file doesn't exist); (2) on 0-byte file emits `event: status\\ndata:{\"status\":\"empty\",...}` then still attaches fs.watchFile so tail engages when the producer starts writing; (3) reads `.gsd-t/transcripts/.index.json` via new `readIndexEntry(projectDir, spawnId)` helper and, if `status` is `done`/`failed`/`stopped`, replays all lines + emits `event: end\\ndata:{\"status\":\"<s>\",\"endedAt\":\"<iso>\"}` + `res.end()` (no tail). Running-spawn path preserves existing replay + byte-offset fs.watchFile dedupe. `test/m42-transcript-sse-replay.test.js` (new, 4/4 pass) covers all four branches via real http.createServer + tmpdir fixture; full suite 1547/1547 pass (baseline 1543 + 4). Producer-side zero-byte bug in `bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs` (post-hoc tee without `--output-format stream-json`) is explicitly out of scope for this quick and untouched per parent-agent directive.\n- 2026-04-21 13:30: [quick] Liveness heartbeat watchdog for unattended supervisor (M43 out-of-band — shipped as a focused quick because M43-D1 probe work uncovered the 270s wall-clock guillotine was too aggressive for legitimate long-running iters). **bin/gsd-t-unattended-heartbeat.cjs** (new,