D0-T2** (`bin/gsd-t-benchmark-orchestrator.js`): CLI `gsd-t benchmark-orchestrator --runs N [--report-path p] [--results-path p] [--fixture-dir p] [--mock-claude p] [--project-dir p]`. Per run: `fs.mkdtempSync` tmp dir → `copyDirSync` fixture → `git init -b main` + baseline commit → spawns `bin/gsd-t-orchestrator.js --milestone M40-bench --project-dir <tmp> --max-parallel 2 --worker-timeout 60000` (orchestrator side) and a single `claude -p --dangerously-skip-permissions --output-format stream-json --verbose --model sonnet` with a sequential-execute prompt as input (in-session side). Captures `Date.now()` deltas per run; collects node version, platform, arch, CPU count, free/total RAM via `collectEnv()`. Writes `.gsd-t/benchmark-results.json` (schema v1: generatedAt, runs, fixtureDir, env, per-run timings + exitCode, summary, verdict) and `docs/m40-benchmark-report.md` (verdict line, per-run table, methodology). Verdict: PASS when `median(orch) ≤ median(insession) × 1.05` AND all runs exit 0; else FAIL with `M40 HALT RECOMMENDED`. Module exports injection points for unit tests — `orchestratorImpl` / `insessionImpl` / `spawnImpl` all overridable. Tolerance `PASS_TOLERANCE = 1.05` exported. **D0-T3** (`test/m40-speed-benchmark.test.js`): 13 unit tests — `parseCliArgs` (defaults + validation), `median` (odd/even/empty), `computeVerdict` (PASS, FAIL-slow, FAIL-any-exit-nonzero), `prepareRun`+`cleanupRun` (fixture copy + git init + tmp cleanup), `renderReportMd` (verdict+rows+methodology), `runBenchmark` smoke (PASS path writes JSON+MD), `runBenchmark` FAIL path, missing-fixture rejection, `runOrchestratorSide` spawnImpl assertions, `runInsessionSide` spawnImpl assertions. Zero real `claude -p` spawns in the test — all injected. Full 3-run verdict remains an operator action (user invokes `gsd-t benchmark-orchestrator --runs 3` with real auth). **Wiring**: `bin/gsd-t.js` help now lists `benchmark-orchestrator`; the subcommand case spawnSyncs the driver with forwarded args