s to halt before D4/D5.\n- 2026-04-19 19:30: [execute] M40 Wave 0 — D1 Tasks 4 + 5 landed (main orchestrator CLI + `gsd-t orchestrate` subcommand). **D1-T4** (`bin/gsd-t-orchestrator.js`): exports `runOrchestrator({projectDir, milestone, maxParallel?, workerTimeoutMs?, logger?, spawnImpl?, runWorkerImpl?})`, `runWaveTasks`, `parseCliArgs`, `atomicWriteJson`. CLI: `gsd-t orchestrate --milestone <id> [--max-parallel N] [--worker-timeout ms] [--project-dir path] [--resume]`. Iterates waves via `groupByWave`; within wave uses a concurrency-capped worker pool (default 3, ceiling 15 per Team Mode §15); strict barrier — wave N+1 never launches until all wave N tasks resolve. Retry policy per completion-signal-contract v1.0.0 §Retry Policy: first FAIL → single retry with \"previous attempt failed\" preamble; second FAIL → halt wave, mark state.json `failed`, exit non-zero (per wave-join-contract v1.0.0 §Failure Semantics). State file at `.gsd-t/orchestrator/state.json` written atomically (tmp + rename) after every task transition; captures milestone, totalTasks, currentWave, per-task {status, startedAt, endedAt, exitCode, durationMs, missing, retryCount}, overall status `running|done|failed`. Emits task lifecycle events to `.gsd-t/events/YYYY-MM-DD.jsonl` reusing the existing event schema: `orchestrator_start`, `wave_start`, `task_start`, `task_done|task_failed`, `wave_done|wave_failed`, `orchestrator_halt|orchestrator_done`. Injects `buildTaskBrief` per spawn; brief built fresh for retry attempts. Test injections: `spawnImpl` (into worker) + `runWorkerImpl` (into orchestrator — lets integration tests stub completion logic without real git commits). **D1-T5** (`bin/gsd-t.js`): added `orchestrate` subcommand case that spawnSyncs `bin/gsd-t-orchestrator.js` with forwarded args; `help` output lists `orchestrate`; existing dispatches (install, status, headless, unattended, etc.) untouched. Smoke tests: `gsd-t help` shows orchestrate; `gsd-t orchestrate --help` prints flag summary; `gsd-t status` still prints current project context. 7/7 integration tests pass (test/m40-orchestrator-main.test.js) including parseCliArgs, empty-project status, single-wave drive-to-done, strict wave barrier ordering (wave 1 waits for all wave 0 dispatches), double-fail halt with failed state.json, events JSONL written. Full suite: **1318/1318** (was 1311, +7). D0-T1 (benchmark fixture) now unblocked — next up. After D0-T1/T2 land, D0-T3 is **THE GATE**: benchmark orchestrator vs in-session; FAIL → halt M40 before D4/D5.\n- 2026-04-19 19:00: [execute] M40 Wave 0 — D2 Task 3 public `buildTaskBrief` API landed. `bin/gsd-t-task-brief.js` exports `buildTaskBrief({milestone, domain, taskId, projectDir, expectedBranch?, maxBytes?}) → string`. Reads `.gsd-t/domains/{domain}/{scope,constraints,tasks}.md`, parses the task entry by number + extracts its `Contract refs:` list, reads only those named contracts (excerpted verbatim from `.gsd-t/contracts/`), reads `completion-signal-contract.md` Done Signal section verbatim for the completion-spec slot, runs stack detection (package.json deps → react/typescript/nextjs/vue/playwright/node-api/tailwind/prisma; Python via requirements.txt / pyproject.toml) and loads matching `templates/stacks/*.md` + universal `_*.md` rules, composes via `renderTemplate`, passes through `compactToTarget`. Deterministic by design — pure fs reads + sorted stack filenames. `extractTask` and `extractSection` helpers exported for unit reuse. 12/12 unit tests pass (test/m40-task-brief.test.js) including determinism (byte-identical on 2 calls), missing-contract throws, missing-domain throws, tight-budget forces stack-rule drop while preserving Task+Done Signal+CWD Invariant, and a self-test against the actual GSD-T repo for D2-T1 (<10KB). Full suite: 1311/1311 (was 1299, +12). **D1-T4 UNBLOCKED** (main orchestrator CLI wave-join loop — next). After D1-T4+T5 land, the D0 benchmark (D0-T1/T2/T3 **GATE**) runs: if FAIL → halt M40 before D4/D5 ever start.\n- 2026-04-19 18:30: [execute] M40 Wave 0 — D2 Tasks 1 + 2 landed (task brief template + compactor) + worker test stabilization. **D2-T1** (`bin/gsd-t-task-brief-template.cjs`): exports `renderPreamble({projectName, milestone, domain, taskId, expectedBranch, projectDir}) → string`, `renderCwdInvariant(projectDir) → string`, `renderTemplate({preamble, taskStatement, scope, constraints, contractExcerpts?, stackRules?, completionSpec, cwdInvariant}) → string`. Frozen section headers (`## Task`, `## Scope`, `## Constraints`, `## Contracts`, `## Stack Rules`, `## Done Signal`, `## CWD Invariant`) per task-brief-contract.md v1.0.0. Contract + stack sections are optional — rendered only when non-empty. 9/9 unit tests pass (test/m40-task-brief-template.test.js). **D2-T2** (`bin/gsd-t-task-brief-compactor.cjs`): exports `compactToTarget(sections, maxBytes) → sections'` and `TaskBriefTooLarge` error. Drop order: `stackRules` → `contractExcerpts` → `constraintsExtra` (droppable). Non-droppable set frozen: `preamble`, `taskStatement`, `scope`, `constraintsMustFollow`, `completionSpec`, `cwdInvariant` — if these alone exceed `maxBytes`, compactor throws `TaskBriefTooLarge` with breakdown. 9/9 unit tests pass (test/m40-task-brief-compactor.test.js). **Test stabilization**: `test/m40-orchestrator-worker.test.js` refactored — happy/fail/invalid-json/env-check tests now use `spawnImpl` EventEmitter mocks; timeout test also converted to mock (kill('SIGTERM') → `exit(null, 'SIGTERM')` 10ms later) eliminating real-sleep dependency. Worker test file now runs in 305ms (was ~1.2s); removed unused `writeMockClaude` helper and `child_process.spawn` import. Full suite: **1299/1299 × 3 consecutive runs clean** — the previously-flaky `telemetry-env-propagation.test.js:178` also stabilized (less fork contention from shell mocks). D1-T4 (main CLI wave-join loop) still blocked on D2-T3 (`buildTaskBrief` public composer). Next: D2-T3 composer → D0-T1 benchmark fixtures → D0-T2 driver → **D0-T3 GATE verdict**.\n- 2026-04-19 17:55: [execute] M40 Wave 0c — D1 Task 3 worker lifecycle (minimal). `bin/gsd-t-orchestrator-worker.cjs` exports `runWorker({task, brief, config, onFrame, env, spawnImpl}) → Promise<{result, exitCode, durationMs, timedOut, stderr}>`. Spawns `claude -p --dangerously-skip-permissions --output-format stream-json --verbose --model {task.model||sonnet}` with cwd=`config.projectDir` and env `GSD_T_PROJECT_DIR`. Writes brief to stdin. Pipes stdout line-by-line through JSON.parse; valid frames → `onFrame(frame)`; unparseable lines → `onFrame({type:\"raw\", line})`. Emits synthetic `task-boundary start` before first frame + `done|failed` after exit (per stream-json-sink-contract v1.0.0). Enforces `config.workerTimeoutMs`: SIGTERM, wait 5s, SIGKILL; writes deterministic `[worker_timeout] task=... budget=...ms elapsed=...ms` via config.logger. Post-exit calls `assertCompletion` from D3-T2 with `ownedPatterns` from `task.ownedPatterns`. Timeout path prepends `worker_exited_via_timeout`; nonzero exit prepends `worker_exit_nonzero`; spawn error returns `missing:[\"spawn_error\"]`. Test-double: `GSD_T_CLAUDE_BIN` env override lets unit tests swap a shell-script mock (happy/fail/hang/invalid-json/env-check). 9/9 unit tests pass (test/m40-orchestrator-worker.test.js). Full suite: 1281/1281 (was 1272, +9). D1 Task 4 (main CLI wave-join loop) blocked on D2-T3 (buildTaskBrief); D2-T1 is next unblocked.\n- 2026-04-19 17:50: [execute] M40 Wave 0b — D1 Task 2 task queue + wave partitioning. `bin/gsd-t-orchestrator-queue.cjs` exports `listDomainTaskFiles`, `parseTasksFile`, `parseDependencies`, `readAllTasks`, `groupByWave(tasks) → Map<waveNum, Task[]>` sorted ascending, `validateNoForwardDeps(tasks)` (per wave-join-contract v1.0.0 §Between-Wave Ordering). Tasks without `**Wave**: N` default to wave 0 (backward-compat safety). Dep parser handles `NONE`/`N/A`/empty, same-domain `Task N` → `domain:TN`, and cross-domain `BLOCKED BY d3-completion-protocol Task 2` →