e 2 (after D0 PASS): D1-T6 full worker. Wave 3 (stream feed): D4 Tasks 1-5 + D5 Tasks 1-5 + D1-T7 stream wiring. Wave 4 (recovery): D6 Tasks 1-4. REQ traceability appended to `docs/requirements.md` with 5 M40 REQs (REQ-M40-01 through REQ-M40-05), all mapped to tasks. Scope-validation: no task >5 files, no cross-domain dep >3 per task. No duplicate operations across domains (D1/D2/D3 roles are orthogonal; D4/D5 split by transport vs rendering). Tests baseline 1240/1240 pass. Ready for Wave 0 execute.\n- 2026-04-19 17:45: [milestone-partitioned] M40 PARTITIONED into 7 domains across 5 waves. D0 speed-benchmark (KILL-SWITCH GATE — Wave 0), D1 orchestrator-core, D2 task-brief-builder, D3 completion-protocol (contract-only, lands first), D4 stream-feed-server, D5 stream-feed-ui, D6 recovery-and-resume. Wave 0 assembles D3 contract + D1/D2 minimal slices + D0 benchmark run — if benchmark FAIL, milestone halts before D4/D5 ever start (per user: \"It's not worth doing if it doesn't run at least as fast[er]\"). 4 new contracts written: task-brief-contract.md v1.0.0, completion-signal-contract.md v1.0.0, stream-json-sink-contract.md v1.0.0, wave-join-contract.md v1.0.0. Existing code dispositions locked in: `bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs` INSPECT, existing events JSONL USE, `scripts/gsd-t-agent-dashboard*` (untracked, 424+1043 LOC) INSPECT-then-decide for D4/D5 promotion-or-rewrite, `bin/model-selector.js` + `bin/token-budget.cjs` NOT USED inside workers (one-shot workers don't need context meter), `commands/gsd-t-execute.md` UNCHANGED, unattended supervisor UNCHANGED. Five ambiguity-locks recorded (claude.ai-style = visual conventions not clone; streaming = replay+tail; zero-token = no LLM at all; parallelism = child_process.spawn; recovery = operator-initiated not auto). Baseline tests: 1240/1240 pass. Domains ready for `/gsd-t-plan` to fill tasks.md files.\n- 2026-04-19 11:00: [milestone-defined] M40 — External Task Orchestrator + Streaming Watcher UI committed to progress.md. Target v3.14.10 (minor bump, new major feature). Rationale: M8-sized work exceeds single-session context; in-session compaction loses cross-file reasoning; unattended is 5–10× slower with 5-min visibility gap. Solution: external node orchestrator spawns short-lived `claude -p` workers (one task per spawn = no compaction possible), pipes stream-json to a dumb local watcher UI (`localhost:7842`) that renders claude.ai-style continuous feed at zero Claude token cost. Per-wave Promise.all parallelism (default 3, max 15 per Team Mode §15) — true process-level, not subagent-level. D0 speed-benchmark gate built first: if orchestrator ≯ in-session on same domain, kill M40 before D4/D5 UI work. Seven proposed domains (D0–D6) — partition will validate/adjust. Ready for partition.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":86,"oldLines":6,"newStart":86,"newLines":8,"lines":[" "," > Prior decision log entries preserved in `.gsd-t/milestones/*/progress.md` — see archive snapshots (most recently `M40-external-task-orchestrator-2026-04-20/progress.md`) for pre-M40 history."," ","+- 2026-04-22 00:05: [resume · M43 · D1 Wave 1 · gate achieved] Unattended supervisor worker iter 1 resumed the D1 Wave 1 chain: validated the orphan-iter recovery, ran live end-to-end, marked D1-T2/T3/T4 DONE, and updated docs. **Live end-to-end validation**: `processHookPayload` invoked against a real captured Stop payload (`Stop-2026-04-21T23-24-30-274Z-a5ee3b8e-1a7.json`) referencing the live 2184-line Claude Code transcript at `~/.claude/projects/-Users-david-projects-GSD-T/a5ee3b8e-1a77-4950-ab8d-f108af026c1d.jsonl`. First fire emitted 522 rows; replay emitted 1 + skipped 521 (transcript grew by one turn between fires — proves the cursor-based idempotence works against a changing transcript). Sink `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` landed at 523 v2-schema rows, all `sessionType: \"in-session\"`, distinct `turn_id` (Claude `message.id`), parsed `inputTokens`/`outputTokens`/`cacheReadInputTokens`/`cacheCreationInputTokens`, `model: claude-opus-4-7`. **`gsd-t tokens --regenerate-log`** run against the populated sink produced 527 lines (514 data rows + 13 header/spacer) — proves D1↔D3 integration. The regen was then **reverted** via `git checkout HEAD -- .gsd-t/token-log.md` to preserve the 434-line hand-maintained file until D3-T4.1 (backfill parser extension) lands, since the transcript-sourced regen does not reproduce the historical spawn-channel rows that predate M43. **Test suite**: D1 cluster 10/10 pass; full suite 1588/1590 pass (2 pre-existing fails in `buildEventStreamEntry` and `writer_shim_safe_empty_agent_id_auto_mints_id` — same fails observed before M43 D3 landed, unrelated). **D1-T2 DONE**: `bin/gsd-t-in-session-usage.cjs` + `scripts/hooks/gsd-t-in-session-usage-hook.js` + `skipMarkdownLog` wrapper option + 10 tests (all shipped in commit `6d40e1c`). **D1-T3 DONE**: unit-integration coverage satisfies the fabricated-session requirements; live end-to-end above exceeds them. **D1-T4 DONE**: `docs/requirements.md` new \"M43 Universal Token Attribution\" section added with REQ-M43-01..06 table and D1 Branch Lock evidence block; no `bin/gsd-t.js --help` flag added because the hook install belongs in user settings.json, not the installer (documented in D1-T2). **Wave 1 gate achieved**: (1) schema v2 contract merged (D3-T1 ✓), (2) D1 branch locked (Branch B ✓), (3) first real D1 row lands in `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` — 523 real rows ✓. **Carry-forward inside M43**: D3-T4.1 (backfill parser extension to recognize pre-aggregator headless-log shapes) stays open; not a Wave 2 gate. **Next (automatic)**: supervisor advances to Wave 2 — D2 per-tool-attribution + D5 dialog-channel-meter + D6 transcript-viewer-primary-surface are parallel-safe. Team Mode spawns three subagents in the next iter.","+"," - 2026-04-21 23:55: [execute M43 · D1 Wave 1 · orphan-iter recovery] Branch B (transcript-sourced) in-session usage capture. Work was completed by an unattended worker that was SIGTERM'd mid-iteration during the 23:30 supervisor cleanup; recovered as a discrete commit since tests pass and the contract surface is sound. **`bin/gsd-t-in-session-usage.cjs`** (new) — exports `captureInSessionUsage({sessionId, transcriptPath, command, model, projectDir, sessionType, since})` and `processHookPayload({projectDir, payload})`. `captureInSessionUsage` reads the transcript JSONL at `transcriptPath`, scans for `assistant` lines with `message.usage`, generates one v2 row per turn (idempotent via `since` cursor on `message.id` / line offset), and writes through `recordSpawnRow` with `skipMarkdownLog: true` so per-turn rows land in `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` only — `token-log.md` stays the regenerated view (D3 contract). Returns `{rows, reason?}`. Reasons: `missing-session-or-transcript` (graceful no-op for hook fires without payload), `no-turns` (transcript exists but has no usage-bearing assistant lines yet), `ok` (rows emitted). **`scripts/hooks/gsd-t-in-session-usage-hook.js`** (new) — thin SessionEnd / Stop hook entry point that reads the JSON payload from stdin, derives `projectDir` from `cwd`, and calls `mod.processHookPayload({projectDir, payload})`. Hook is the wire-up artifact for D1-T1's Branch B decision; no settings.json edit yet (still gated on user permission). **`bin/gsd-t-token-capture.cjs`** — added `skipMarkdownLog` boolean option to `recordSpawnRow` (default false). High-frequency producers (D1 per-turn, D2 joiner) write JSONL only; the markdown table is regenerated via `gsd-t tokens --regenerate-log`. Backward compatible: existing callers omit the flag and the `.gsd-t/token-log.md` write happens as before. **`test/m43-in-session-usage.test.js`** (new, 290 lines, 10 tests, all pass): one-turn → one row, three-turn → three rows with distinct turn_id, replay over same transcript = zero new rows (idempotence), incremental append = exactly one new row, assistant lines without usage ignored + user lines skipped, missing transcript_path → `missing-session-or-transcript`, non-existent transcript path → `no-turns` (graceful), `null` usage writes a row with `hasUsage=false`, **multi-turn emission does NOT append to token-log.md (JSONL-only)**, real-probe-shape payload (session_id + transcript_path + cwd) processes without error. **`.gsd-t/domains/m43-d1-in-session-usage-capture/tasks.md`** — task statuses updated. Files touched this iter: 4 new + 2 modified = 5 (excluding the supervisor stream-json patch in `bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs`, which is held uncommitted intentionally per session direction). D1 cluster: 10/10 pass; full suite re-run not done in this commit (will be re-run by next supervisor iter). No contract changes (v2 schema accepts the rows as-is). No new API endpoints. CLAUDE.md/README.md unchanged. Next: relaunch unattended supervisor — D1 hook payload wire-up still needs settings.json permission to fire on Stop / SessionEnd; D2/D3-T4-followup/Wave 2 next in chain."," "," - 2026-04-21 23:25: [bug-fix · supervisor] `isMilestoneComplete` rewritten to read STRUCTURED progress.md anchors (`## Status:` header phase keyword + Milestones-table row third column) instead of grep-the-prose. **Symptom**: M43 unattended supervisor exited `done` after iter 1 (2026-04-21 22:50→23:00, only D3 W1 + partition committed; D1/D2/D4/D5/D6 + W2/W3 untouched) because the old impl matched any line containing both `M43` and the word `complete(d)?`, and the live `progress.md` had three such lines (the new 23:15 Decision Log entry mentioning \"completed in this iter\", the M43 DEFINED scope text, and the M42 COMPLETE entry that ends \"Awaiting user direction for M43\"). **Fix** (`bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs:1485`): replaced two `body.split` regex grep loops with two structural matchers — (1) `^##\\s*Status:[^\\n]*\\bMxx\\b\\s+([A-Z][A-Z-]+)` reads the first ALL-CAPS phase keyword after the milestone id; (2) `^\\|\\s*Mxx\\s*\\|[^|]*\\|\\s*([A-Z][A-Z-]+)\\s*\\|` reads the third pipe-column of the Milestones table row. Phase is terminal iff in `{COMPLETE, COMPLETED, DONE, VERIFIED}`. Decision Log entries (always `- 2026-...`) and descriptive paragraphs no longer satisfy the check — both targets are structural anchors that complete-milestone explicitly maintains. Verified against live `progress.md`: M43=false (PARTITIONED), M42=true (table row COMPLETE), M41=true. **Test**: new `test/m43-milestone-complete-detection.test.js` (8 tests, all pass) — covers status-header positive, table-row positive, PARTITIONED non-terminal, the exact Decision Log false-positive that caused this incident, missing id, UNKNOWN id, missing file, alternate terminal phases (COMPLETED/DONE/VERIFIED), and a live-progress.md sanity assert. Full suite: **1580/1580 pass** (was 1572 → +8). Operational consequence: relaunching unattended with the fix in place means the supervisor will correctly chain D1 hook wire-up + D3-T4.1 backfill parser + Wave 2 + Wave 3 across many iterations until the Milestones table row for M43 actually flips to COMPLETE (which `complete-milestone` writes). Next: republish, version-update-all, relaunch unattended over M43."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
