{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0155wnfsUB6sjiv9S1Secsqa","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/david/projects/GSD-T/.gsd-t/progress.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"96e7dda7-b960-48d1-b1cb-90373ff412c9","uuid":"02038697-379d-4d9a-a22b-db7a1bd572e8","timestamp":"2026-04-21T23:36:36.607Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/david/projects/GSD-T/.gsd-t/progress.md","oldString":"- 2026-04-22 00:05: [resume · M43 · D1 Wave 1 · gate achieved]","newString":"- 2026-04-21 16:36: [resume · M43 · D1 Wave 1 · gate achieved]","originalFile":"# GSD-T Progress\n\n## Project: GSD-T Framework (@tekyzinc/gsd-t)\n## Status: M43 PARTITIONED — Token Attribution & Always-Headless Inversion (target v3.17.10)\n## Date: 2026-04-21\n## Version: 3.16.12\n\n## Current Milestone\n\n**M43 Token Attribution & Always-Headless Inversion** — DEFINED (6 domains). Target: v3.17.10.\n\n**Goal**: Make every token attributable to a specific tool / command / domain, and lock the framework to a single rule: **the in-session channel is reserved for human↔Claude dialog. All tool-using work spawns. The visualizer is the watching surface.** No flags, no thresholds, no opt-outs — there is no \"in-session mode\" for commands to enter.\n\n**Rationale (revised 2026-04-21)**: The original framing (\"headless when pressure is high, in-session otherwise\") is wrong. A circuit breaker only makes sense when the default is \"in-session, sometimes headless.\" Once the default is \"always headless, dialog-only stays in-session,\" there is nothing to trip — the spawn already happened. The dialog channel exists for *thinking together*; the visualizer (`:7433`) exists for *watching the doing*. Conflating them is what produced the bee-poc compaction pathology (agent `b94ca63f`, 3 compactions in one workday). The fix isn't smarter routing — it's a clean separation of channels.\n\n**Scope — Part A: Universal Token Attribution**\n- **D1 per-turn in-session usage capture** — Capture token usage for every turn of the dialog channel (the only thing still running in-session under this model). Hook-based if Claude Code exposes `usage` on `Stop` / `SessionEnd` (probe shipped `f94857b`, branch decision pending); otherwise extend the M42 transcript tee to interactive sessions and parse the same stream-json `result` frame the M40 D4 aggregator already understands. Output: per-turn rows into `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` with `turn_id`, `session_id`, `command`, `model`, `usage{...}`. Headless spawns are already covered by M41.\n- **D2 per-tool attribution** — `bin/gsd-t-tool-attribution.cjs` joins the events stream (`.gsd-t/events/*.jsonl`, which carries every tool-call request/response with `turn_id`) against the per-turn usage JSONL from D1, then attributes the turn's usage across the turn's tool_calls by output-byte ratio. Ships `gsd-t tool-cost --group-by tool|command|domain [--since YYYY-MM-DD] [--milestone Mxx] [--format table|json]`. Under the always-headless model this matters *more*, not less, because spawned work is now the dominant cost and operators need to slice it.\n- **D3 sink unification + backfill** — Define one canonical token-row schema (extending M40 D4 schema v1) and route every producer through it: M36 heartbeat, M40 aggregator, D1 dialog capture, D2 joiner. `.gsd-t/token-log.md` becomes a *regenerated view* (`gsd-t tokens --regenerate-log`), not a hand-maintained markdown table. Backfill the existing 64 `Tokens=0` rows from `.gsd-t/events/*.jsonl` + `.gsd-t/headless-*.log` (M41 D3 backfiller existed but was never run against the historical log).\n\n**Scope — Part B: Always-Headless Inversion (revised — channel separation, not threshold flip)**\n- **D4 always-headless command spawn (no flag, no threshold)** — Strip the \"headless when over context band\" logic from ~14 command files (`execute`, `wave`, `integrate`, `quick`, `debug`, `verify`, `complete-milestone`, `test-sync`, `scan`, `gap-analysis`, `populate`, `feature`, `project`, `partition`). Every command spawns. Period. **No `--in-session` opt-out, no `--headless` flag, no low-water mark, no context-meter-driven branching at spawn time.** The only thing that runs in the dialog channel is the `/gsd` router itself, which always spawns the actual command. Removes ~3 layers of conditional routing logic and the cognitive load of \"which mode is this command in right now.\"\n- **D5 dialog-channel meter (router-only, replaces the deleted compaction-pressure circuit breaker)** — Originally scoped as a turn-over-turn circuit breaker that would refuse to start in-session commands when growth predicted `/compact`. Under the new channel model there are no in-session commands to refuse. **D5 collapses to a much smaller utility**: a turn-over-turn growth meter on the router itself (since the router is what stays in-session). When dialog growth predicts `/compact` within N turns, surface a one-line warning so the user can `/clear` or wrap the conversation deliberately. Pure read/warn — never refuses, never reroutes (there's nothing to reroute to). Lives in `bin/runway-estimator.cjs` as a small extension, not a new module.\n- **D6 transcript viewer as the primary surface (not a hint)** — Promote the M42 `:7433` transcript viewer from \"useful for unattended runs\" / \"URL hint alongside in-session option\" to **the** surface. Every spawn prints `view at http://127.0.0.1:7433/transcript/{spawn-id}` because that's where the work lives now. The dashboard auto-launches on first command spawn if not already running (port resolved via the project-hashed default from the multi-project isolation quick `df34eb2`). No `--in-session` print path because there is no `--in-session` mode.\n\n**Tradeoff acknowledged**: Spawning even tiny work (a single Read, one Bash) has overhead — orchestrator startup, transcript file, dashboard registration. Worth it for clean channel separation and uniform observability. If overhead bites, the answer is to make the spawn faster (M40-style fast spawn), not to make a threshold smarter.\n\n**Out of scope (deferred)**:\n- Intervene / SIGSTOP-inject (already deferred from M42).\n- Migrating away from `usage`-bearing streams if Claude Code stops emitting them (separate forensic milestone if the contract breaks).\n- Auto-`/clear` on dialog meter trip — D5 only warns; the user decides when to wrap the dialog.\n\n**Contracts touched**:\n- `metrics-schema-contract.md` v1 → v2 (adds `turn_id`, `session_id`, `tool_attribution[]`; **removes** `compaction_pressure` from the original v2 sketch — D5 collapses, no schema field needed)\n- `stream-json-sink-contract.md` v1.1.0 → v1.2.0 (formalize the dialog-channel hook entry-point alongside the existing headless-spawn entry-point)\n- New: `tool-attribution-contract.md` (output-byte ratio algorithm, tie-breaker rules, missing-data handling)\n- `headless-default-contract.md` v1.0.0 → v2.0.0 (always-headless rule; **delete** `--in-session` opt-out + low-water mark from the v1 spec; document the channel-separation invariant: dialog = router only, everything else spawns)\n\n**Success criteria**:\n1. Every spawn writes a per-turn row to `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` with usage parsed (never `0`, never `N/A` — `—` only when the upstream envelope itself is missing).\n2. `gsd-t tool-cost --group-by tool` shows non-zero attribution for at least Bash, Read, Edit, Grep, Task across the last 30 days of repo activity (after backfill).\n3. `.gsd-t/token-log.md` is fully regeneratable from `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` (delete + regenerate produces a byte-identical file modulo timestamp ordering).\n4. **No command file accepts `--in-session` or `--headless` flags.** Default invocation of any of the 14 listed commands spawns. Grep for `--in-session` in `commands/*.md` returns zero matches after D4.\n5. Dashboard URL is printed at every spawn; visiting it shows the live transcript without operator action beyond clicking the link.\n6. D5 dialog meter fires a one-line warning on a synthetic high-growth fixture in the router context; never refuses, never reroutes.\n\n**Assessment**: MEDIUM (was COMPLEX — D5 collapse and D4 simplification each removed roughly half their original scope). Recommended flow: `partition` → `discuss` (only D1 hook-vs-tee branch needs discussion now; D5 heuristic is no longer in scope) → `plan` → `execute` (waves) → `integrate` → `verify` → `complete-milestone` → tag v3.17.10.\n\n**Previous milestone (M42) retained for reference below** (M42 Live Spawn Transcript Viewer — COMPLETE, v3.16.10 tagged 2026-04-20, 3 domains, 29 M42 tests, 1522/1522 suite).\n\n## Milestones\n\n| # | Milestone | Status | Version | Domains |\n|---|-----------|--------|---------|---------|\n| M43 | Token Attribution & Always-Headless Inversion | PARTITIONED | 3.17.10 (target) | 6 domains across 2 themes, 3 waves (W1 D3+D1 foundation · W2 D2+D5+D6 parallel · W3 D4 alone). **Part A — Universal Token Attribution**: D1 per-turn dialog-channel usage capture (hook-based if Claude Code exposes usage on Stop/SessionEnd — probe shipped `f94857b` — else extend M42 transcript tee to interactive); D2 per-tool attribution (`bin/gsd-t-tool-attribution.cjs` joins events JSONL + token-usage JSONL by `turn_id`, attributes by output-byte ratio; `gsd-t tool-cost --group-by tool|command|domain`); D3 sink unification + backfill (canonical schema v2, `token-log.md` regenerated view, backfill 64 historical Tokens=0 rows). **Part B — Always-Headless Inversion (channel separation)**: D4 strip headless/in-session branching from ~14 command files — every command spawns, no `--in-session` flag, no `--headless` flag, no low-water mark; D5 collapses from compaction-pressure circuit breaker to a router-only dialog meter (warn on growth; never refuses/reroutes); D6 transcript viewer (`:7433`) as **the** primary surface — URL printed at every spawn, dashboard auto-launches if not running. Contracts: metrics-schema v1→v2 (drops `compaction_pressure` field from original sketch), stream-json-sink v1.1.0→v1.2.0, new tool-attribution-contract, headless-default v1.0.0→v2.0.0 (**deletes** `--in-session` opt-out, documents channel-separation invariant). |\n| M42 | Live Spawn Transcript Viewer | COMPLETE | 3.16.10 | 3 domains. D1 stream-json tee capture (transcript-tee.cjs, orchestrator-worker tee, unattended post-hoc tee); D2 SSE route + ndjson→HTML renderer (`/transcript/:id`, `/transcript/:id/stream`, `gsd-t-transcript.html` Claude-Code-style renderer with auto-scroll); D3 sidebar tree + kill controls (parent-indented tree, status dots, POST `/transcript/:id/kill`). 29 M42-specific tests; 1522/1522 suite pass. Intervene/SIGSTOP deferred to follow-up milestone. |\n| M41 | Universal Token Capture Across GSD-T | COMPLETE | 3.15.10 | 5 domains, 3 waves. Wave 1: D1 token-capture-wrapper (3 tasks). Wave 2 parallel: D2 command-file-doc-ripple (4 tasks × 20 command files + 2 CLAUDE files), D3 historical-backfill (4 tasks, `bin/gsd-t-token-backfill.cjs` + `gsd-t backfill-tokens` CLI). Wave 3 parallel: D4 token-dashboard (4 tasks, `gsd-t tokens` + status integration), D5 enforcement (5 tasks, linter + opt-in hook + CLAUDE rule). Reuses M40 D4 aggregator + schema v1 — no new contracts. |\n| M40 | External Task Orchestrator + Streaming Watcher UI | COMPLETE | 3.14.10 | 7 domains, 30 tasks. D0 benchmark gate PASSED; Waves 1–4 shipped; 1421/1421 tests; operator D0 result 0.72× wall-clock vs in-session. |\n| M39 | Fast Unattended + Universal Watch-Progress Tree | COMPLETE | 3.13.10 | 3 domains: D2 progress-watch, D3 parallel-exec, D4 cache-warm-pacing |\n| M38 | Headless-by-Default + Meter Reduction | COMPLETE | 3.12.10 | 5 domains in 2 waves: Wave 1 sequential (m38-headless-spawn-default → m38-meter-reduction); Wave 2 parallel (m38-unattended-event-stream + m38-router-conversational + m38-cleanup-and-docs) |\n| M37 | Universal Context Auto-Pause | COMPLETE | 3.11.10 | Archived (1 domain: m37-auto-pause; context-meter-contract v1.2.0; 5 command files updated; 1228/1228 tests) |\n| M36 | Cross-Platform Unattended Supervisor Loop | COMPLETE | 3.10.10 | Archived (6 domains) |\n| M35 | No Silent Degradation + Surgical Model Escalation + Token Telemetry | COMPLETE | 2.76.10 | Archived (7 domains; 38 tasks) |\n| M34 | Context Meter | COMPLETE | 2.75.10 | Archived |\n\n## Completed Milestones\n\n| Milestone | Version | Completed | Tag | Summary |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|-----|---------|\n| M42 Live Spawn Transcript Viewer | 3.16.10 | 2026-04-20 | v3.16.10 | 3 domains (D1 stream-json-tee + D2 SSE-renderer + D3 sidebar-kill); 29 M42 tests; 1522/1522 suite; Claude-Code-style per-spawn transcript UI on `:7433` with parent-indented tree, auto-scroll, kill button. Intervene/SIGSTOP deferred. |\n| M41 Universal Token Capture Across GSD-T | 3.15.10 | 2026-04-20 | v3.15.10 | 5 domains (D1 wrapper + D2 doc-ripple 20 commands + D3 backfill + D4 dashboard + D5 enforcement); 1479/1479 tests; `bin/gsd-t-token-capture.cjs` with `captureSpawn`/`recordSpawnRow`; `gsd-t tokens` + `gsd-t capture-lint`; opt-in pre-commit hook; `CLAUDE.md` MUST rule. |\n| M40 External Task Orchestrator + Streaming Watcher UI | 3.14.10 | 2026-04-20 | v3.14.10 | 7 domains (D0 speed-benchmark + D1 orchestrator-core + D2 task-brief-builder + D3 completion-protocol + D4 stream-feed-server + D5 stream-feed-ui + D6 recovery-and-resume); 30 tasks; 1421/1421 tests; operator D0 gate 0.72× wall-clock vs in-session (226s vs 316s); 4 contracts (stream-json-sink v1.1.0, wave-join, completion-signal, metrics-schema). |\n| M39 Fast Unattended + Universal Watch-Progress Tree | 3.13.10 | 2026-04-18 | v3.13.10 | 3 domains (D2 progress-watch + D3 parallel-exec + D4 cache-warm-pacing); 1240/1240 tests; Red Team GRUDGING PASS; plus 6 follow-on patches v3.13.11–3.13.16 |\n| M38 Headless-by-Default + Meter Reduction | 3.12.10 | 2026-04-17 | v3.12.10 | Headless spawn default across 7 commands; context meter reduced to single-band; 7 commands deleted; event stream JSONL; smart router intent classifier; 5 contracts folded; 1176/1177 tests |\n| M37 Universal Context Auto-Pause | 3.11.10 | 2026-04-16 | v3.11.10 | Strengthened context meter additionalContext from suggestion to MANDATORY STOP instruction; context-meter-contract v1.2.0; CLAUDE-global Universal Auto-Pause Rule section; Step 0.2 in 5 loop commands; 1228/1228 tests |\n| M36 Cross-Platform Unattended Supervisor Loop | 3.10.10 | 2026-04-15 | v3.10.10 | Detached supervisor relay for 24h+ unattended milestone execution; 3 new slash commands (unattended/unattended-watch/unattended-stop); ScheduleWakeup(270s) in-session watch loop; /clear+/resume auto-reattach via Step 0; cross-platform (macOS/Linux/Windows except sleep-prevention); safety rails (gutter/blocker/timeout); 1226/1226 tests |\n| M35 Runway-Protected Execution | 2.76.10 | 2026-04-15 | v2.76.10 | Removed silent quality degradation; surgical per-phase model selection; pre-flight runway estimator with headless auto-spawn; 18-field per-spawn token telemetry; detect-only optimization backlog; 985/985 tests |\n| M34 Context Meter | 2.75.10 | 2026-04-14 | v2.75.10 | Real context-window measurement via Anthropic count_tokens API; replaces task-counter proxy entirely; 941/941 tests |\n\nOlder milestones (M33 and earlier) archived under `.gsd-t/milestones/` — see directory listing for the full index.\n\n## Blockers\n<!-- No active blockers -->\n\n## Decision Log\n\n> Prior decision log entries preserved in `.gsd-t/milestones/*/progress.md` — see archive snapshots (most recently `M40-external-task-orchestrator-2026-04-20/progress.md`) for pre-M40 history.\n\n- 2026-04-22 00:05: [resume · M43 · D1 Wave 1 · gate achieved] Unattended supervisor worker iter 1 resumed the D1 Wave 1 chain: validated the orphan-iter recovery, ran live end-to-end, marked D1-T2/T3/T4 DONE, and updated docs. **Live end-to-end validation**: `processHookPayload` invoked against a real captured Stop payload (`Stop-2026-04-21T23-24-30-274Z-a5ee3b8e-1a7.json`) referencing the live 2184-line Claude Code transcript at `~/.claude/projects/-Users-david-projects-GSD-T/a5ee3b8e-1a77-4950-ab8d-f108af026c1d.jsonl`. First fire emitted 522 rows; replay emitted 1 + skipped 521 (transcript grew by one turn between fires — proves the cursor-based idempotence works against a changing transcript). Sink `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` landed at 523 v2-schema rows, all `sessionType: \"in-session\"`, distinct `turn_id` (Claude `message.id`), parsed `inputTokens`/`outputTokens`/`cacheReadInputTokens`/`cacheCreationInputTokens`, `model: claude-opus-4-7`. **`gsd-t tokens --regenerate-log`** run against the populated sink produced 527 lines (514 data rows + 13 header/spacer) — proves D1↔D3 integration. The regen was then **reverted** via `git checkout HEAD -- .gsd-t/token-log.md` to preserve the 434-line hand-maintained file until D3-T4.1 (backfill parser extension) lands, since the transcript-sourced regen does not reproduce the historical spawn-channel rows that predate M43. **Test suite**: D1 cluster 10/10 pass; full suite 1588/1590 pass (2 pre-existing fails in `buildEventStreamEntry` and `writer_shim_safe_empty_agent_id_auto_mints_id` — same fails observed before M43 D3 landed, unrelated). **D1-T2 DONE**: `bin/gsd-t-in-session-usage.cjs` + `scripts/hooks/gsd-t-in-session-usage-hook.js` + `skipMarkdownLog` wrapper option + 10 tests (all shipped in commit `6d40e1c`). **D1-T3 DONE**: unit-integration coverage satisfies the fabricated-session requirements; live end-to-end above exceeds them. **D1-T4 DONE**: `docs/requirements.md` new \"M43 Universal Token Attribution\" section added with REQ-M43-01..06 table and D1 Branch Lock evidence block; no `bin/gsd-t.js --help` flag added because the hook install belongs in user settings.json, not the installer (documented in D1-T2). **Wave 1 gate achieved**: (1) schema v2 contract merged (D3-T1 ✓), (2) D1 branch locked (Branch B ✓), (3) first real D1 row lands in `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` — 523 real rows ✓. **Carry-forward inside M43**: D3-T4.1 (backfill parser extension to recognize pre-aggregator headless-log shapes) stays open; not a Wave 2 gate. **Next (automatic)**: supervisor advances to Wave 2 — D2 per-tool-attribution + D5 dialog-channel-meter + D6 transcript-viewer-primary-surface are parallel-safe. Team Mode spawns three subagents in the next iter.\n\n- 2026-04-21 23:55: [execute M43 · D1 Wave 1 · orphan-iter recovery] Branch B (transcript-sourced) in-session usage capture. Work was completed by an unattended worker that was SIGTERM'd mid-iteration during the 23:30 supervisor cleanup; recovered as a discrete commit since tests pass and the contract surface is sound. **`bin/gsd-t-in-session-usage.cjs`** (new) — exports `captureInSessionUsage({sessionId, transcriptPath, command, model, projectDir, sessionType, since})` and `processHookPayload({projectDir, payload})`. `captureInSessionUsage` reads the transcript JSONL at `transcriptPath`, scans for `assistant` lines with `message.usage`, generates one v2 row per turn (idempotent via `since` cursor on `message.id` / line offset), and writes through `recordSpawnRow` with `skipMarkdownLog: true` so per-turn rows land in `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` only — `token-log.md` stays the regenerated view (D3 contract). Returns `{rows, reason?}`. Reasons: `missing-session-or-transcript` (graceful no-op for hook fires without payload), `no-turns` (transcript exists but has no usage-bearing assistant lines yet), `ok` (rows emitted). **`scripts/hooks/gsd-t-in-session-usage-hook.js`** (new) — thin SessionEnd / Stop hook entry point that reads the JSON payload from stdin, derives `projectDir` from `cwd`, and calls `mod.processHookPayload({projectDir, payload})`. Hook is the wire-up artifact for D1-T1's Branch B decision; no settings.json edit yet (still gated on user permission). **`bin/gsd-t-token-capture.cjs`** — added `skipMarkdownLog` boolean option to `recordSpawnRow` (default false). High-frequency producers (D1 per-turn, D2 joiner) write JSONL only; the markdown table is regenerated via `gsd-t tokens --regenerate-log`. Backward compatible: existing callers omit the flag and the `.gsd-t/token-log.md` write happens as before. **`test/m43-in-session-usage.test.js`** (new, 290 lines, 10 tests, all pass): one-turn → one row, three-turn → three rows with distinct turn_id, replay over same transcript = zero new rows (idempotence), incremental append = exactly one new row, assistant lines without usage ignored + user lines skipped, missing transcript_path → `missing-session-or-transcript`, non-existent transcript path → `no-turns` (graceful), `null` usage writes a row with `hasUsage=false`, **multi-turn emission does NOT append to token-log.md (JSONL-only)**, real-probe-shape payload (session_id + transcript_path + cwd) processes without error. **`.gsd-t/domains/m43-d1-in-session-usage-capture/tasks.md`** — task statuses updated. Files touched this iter: 4 new + 2 modified = 5 (excluding the supervisor stream-json patch in `bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs`, which is held uncommitted intentionally per session direction). D1 cluster: 10/10 pass; full suite re-run not done in this commit (will be re-run by next supervisor iter). No contract changes (v2 schema accepts the rows as-is). No new API endpoints. CLAUDE.md/README.md unchanged. Next: relaunch unattended supervisor — D1 hook payload wire-up still needs settings.json permission to fire on Stop / SessionEnd; D2/D3-T4-followup/Wave 2 next in chain.\n\n- 2026-04-21 23:25: [bug-fix · supervisor] `isMilestoneComplete` rewritten to read STRUCTURED progress.md anchors (`## Status:` header phase keyword + Milestones-table row third column) instead of grep-the-prose. **Symptom**: M43 unattended supervisor exited `done` after iter 1 (2026-04-21 22:50→23:00, only D3 W1 + partition committed; D1/D2/D4/D5/D6 + W2/W3 untouched) because the old impl matched any line containing both `M43` and the word `complete(d)?`, and the live `progress.md` had three such lines (the new 23:15 Decision Log entry mentioning \"completed in this iter\", the M43 DEFINED scope text, and the M42 COMPLETE entry that ends \"Awaiting user direction for M43\"). **Fix** (`bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs:1485`): replaced two `body.split` regex grep loops with two structural matchers — (1) `^##\\s*Status:[^\\n]*\\bMxx\\b\\s+([A-Z][A-Z-]+)` reads the first ALL-CAPS phase keyword after the milestone id; (2) `^\\|\\s*Mxx\\s*\\|[^|]*\\|\\s*([A-Z][A-Z-]+)\\s*\\|` reads the third pipe-column of the Milestones table row. Phase is terminal iff in `{COMPLETE, COMPLETED, DONE, VERIFIED}`. Decision Log entries (always `- 2026-...`) and descriptive paragraphs no longer satisfy the check — both targets are structural anchors that complete-milestone explicitly maintains. Verified against live `progress.md`: M43=false (PARTITIONED), M42=true (table row COMPLETE), M41=true. **Test**: new `test/m43-milestone-complete-detection.test.js` (8 tests, all pass) — covers status-header positive, table-row positive, PARTITIONED non-terminal, the exact Decision Log false-positive that caused this incident, missing id, UNKNOWN id, missing file, alternate terminal phases (COMPLETED/DONE/VERIFIED), and a live-progress.md sanity assert. Full suite: **1580/1580 pass** (was 1572 → +8). Operational consequence: relaunching unattended with the fix in place means the supervisor will correctly chain D1 hook wire-up + D3-T4.1 backfill parser + Wave 2 + Wave 3 across many iterations until the Milestones table row for M43 actually flips to COMPLETE (which `complete-milestone` writes). Next: republish, version-update-all, relaunch unattended over M43.\n\n- 2026-04-21 23:15: [quick · M43-D6-pre] Live transcript tee — the M42 D1 post-hoc transcript write was replaced with a streaming path so `/transcript/:id/stream` renders worker output as it