 `_buildJsonlRecord` + `recordSpawnRow` + `captureSpawn` now pass through optional v2 fields (`sessionId` → `session_id`, `turnId` → `turn_id`, `sessionType`, `toolAttribution` → `tool_attribution`, `compactionPressure` → `compaction_pressure`). Fields only emit when explicitly provided — existing callers unchanged (v1-shape call produces a row with `schemaVersion: 2` and no v2 fields present, which is a valid v2 row per contract §Backward compatibility). Empty `toolAttribution: []` is omitted rather than emitted as `[]` (keeps historical rows indistinguishable between \"no attribution available\" and \"attribution = nothing\"). **D3-T3 regenerate-log**: new `bin/gsd-t-token-regenerate-log.cjs` (~110 lines, zero deps, reuses `NEW_HEADER`/`NEW_SEP`/`_formatTokensCell` from the capture module); reads `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl`, sorts deterministically by `startedAt` asc → `session_id` asc → `turn_id` asc (numeric when both parse, lex otherwise), writes `.gsd-t/token-log.md`. Exports `regenerateLog`/`renderMarkdown`/`sortRows`. Registered as `gsd-t tokens --regenerate-log` in `bin/gsd-t.js` (help text updated). **D3-T5 tests**: `test/m43-schema-v2.test.js` — 9 tests, all pass: backward-compat (v1-caller yields v2 row minus new fields), v2 pass-through (session_id/turn_id/sessionType), tool_attribution + compaction_pressure pass-through, empty array omission, regenerate idempotence (byte-identical on repeated run), deterministic sort including numeric turn_id ordering (a/2 before a/10 before b/2), missing-usage → `—`, empty JSONL → header-only file, schemaVersion=1 rows render correctly. Two existing M41 assertions updated from `assert.equal(rec.schemaVersion, 1)` → `assert.equal(rec.schemaVersion, capture.SCHEMA_VERSION)` (v2 is additive — v1-shape callers keep working, just tagged with the current version number). **D3-T4 dry-run backfill finding**: `node bin/gsd-t.js backfill-tokens --dry-run` scanned 42 historical files (`.gsd-t/events/*.jsonl` + `.gsd-t/headless-*.log`) and parsed **0 envelopes** — the shipped headless `.log` files are pure human-readable Claude output without the stream-json `result` frame the backfiller's parser expects. `scripts/gsd-t-token-aggregator.js::processFrame` parses the right shape but the headless logs in this repo were produced by a pre-aggregator tee path. **Consequence**: `gsd-t tokens --regenerate-log` run against the live repo right now would overwrite the 434-line hand-maintained `.gsd-t/token-log.md` with a 5-line file (the JSONL currently has only 2 rows). Verified empirically (then immediately `git checkout HEAD -- .gsd-t/token-log.md` restored). **Contract invariant holds**: under v2, `token-log.md` IS a regenerated view — the precondition is a fully-backfilled JSONL, and the backfiller parser needs extension before that precondition can be met. Parser extension is out of D3 Wave 1 scope (D3-T4 acceptance was \"backfill dry-run reports the historical rows\" — it ran, reported zero matches, and surfaced the exact parser gap the M43 partition's D3 scope anticipates). Follow-up task carried in D3 domain: extend `bin/gsd-t-token-backfill.cjs` regex/line-parser to recognize the pre-aggregator headless-log banner + non-JSON prose shape. Until that lands, `tokens --regenerate-log` should only be run after the operator has backfilled JSONL from a known-good source (or accepts the truncation). Files touched: `bin/gsd-t-token-capture.cjs` (+18 lines v2 pass-through), `bin/gsd-t-token-regenerate-log.cjs` (new, 110 lines), `bin/gsd-t.js` (+13 lines `--regenerate-log` branch in `tokens` case), `test/m43-schema-v2.test.js` (new, 9 tests), `test/m41-token-capture.test.js` + `test/m41-token-backfill.test.js` (1 assertion each: v1 → `SCHEMA_VERSION` constant), `docs/architecture.md` (+15 lines Token Pipeline block under Context Observability). Token cluster tests: **60/60 pass** (was 51 → +9 new). Full suite: **1569/1571 pass** (2 pre-existing fails — `event-stream.test.js::buildEventStreamEntry` + `watch-progress-writer.test.js::writer_shim_safe_empty_agent_id_auto_mints_id` — confirmed unrelated by stash + re-run against HEAD; same 2 fails). D3-T6 doc ripple: this entry + architecture.md update land in the same commit. CLAUDE.md Observability block not updated — wrapper signature is additively backward-compatible, existing \"Pattern A\"/\"Pattern B\" examples remain correct. No new API endpoints, no schema changes beyond the already-committed v2 contract bump, no requirement changes. Next: D1-T1 still BLOCKED on settings.json permission for hook wire-up (gate on Wave 2); D3-T4 backfill parser extension carried forward as a sub-task inside D3.\n\n- 2026-04-21 22:55: [quick · M43-D6-pre] Dashboard root page (`/`) gained a \"▶ Live Stream\" button in the header that fetches `/transcripts` every 10s and links to the latest spawn at `/transcript/:spawnId`. Live spawns (status not in `done|stopped|failed|crashed`) preferred over historical; falls back to most-recent if none live. Button ships disabled (label \"▶ Live Stream (no spawns yet)\") and self-enables once `/transcripts` returns at least one entry. Files touched: `scripts/gsd-t-dashboard.html` (CSS `.livestream-btn`, anchor in `.hdr`, 25-line poll IIFE) + `test/dashboard-server.test.js` (regression test serving the real shipped HTML, asserts button id, disabled-by-default class, `/transcripts` reference, `/transcript/${spawnId}` navigation). Test added: 1 (passes). This is a precursor to M43 D6 (\"transcript viewer as the primary surface\") — not yet under D6 scope numbering since M43 execute hasn't started; treat as a quick patch that D6 inherits and extends.\n\n- 2026-04-21 22:36: [partition M43 · unattended iter 1] M43 partition.md rewritten from the stale M39 content to the revised 6-domain / 3-wave plan. **Wave 1** (Foundation) — D3 (schema v2 sink) + D1 (dialog-channel capture; D1-T1 probe already installed `f94857b`, branch lock blocked on settings.json hook wire-up permission); gates on v2 con