rker.cjs` exports `runWorker({task, brief, config, onFrame, env, spawnImpl}) → Promise<{result, exitCode, durationMs, timedOut, stderr}>`. Spawns `claude -p --dangerously-skip-permissions --output-format stream-json --verbose --model {task.model||sonnet}` with cwd=`config.projectDir` and env `GSD_T_PROJECT_DIR`. Writes brief to stdin. Pipes stdout line-by-line through JSON.parse; valid frames → `onFrame(frame)`; unparseable lines → `onFrame({type:\"raw\", line})`. Emits synthetic `task-boundary start` before first frame + `done|failed` after exit (per stream-json-sink-contract v1.0.0). Enforces `config.workerTimeoutMs`: SIGTERM, wait 5s, SIGKILL; writes deterministic `[worker_timeout] task=... budget=...ms elapsed=...ms` via config.logger. Post-exit calls `assertCompletion` from D3-T2 with `ownedPatterns` from `task.ownedPatterns`. Timeout path prepends `worker_exited_via_timeout`; nonzero exit prepends `worker_exit_nonzero`; spawn error returns `missing:[\"spawn_error\"]`. Test-double: `GSD_T_CLAUDE_BIN` env override lets unit tests swap a shell-script mock (happy/fail/hang/invalid-json/env-check). 9/9 unit tests pass (test/m40-orchestrator-worker.test.js). Full suite: 1281/1281 (was 1272, +9). D1 Task 4 (main CLI wave-join loop) blocked on D2-T3 (buildTaskBrief); D2-T1 is next unblocked.\n- 2026-04-19 17:50: [execute] M40 Wave 0b — D1 Task 2 task queue + wave partitioning. `bin/gsd-t-orchestrator-queue.cjs` exports `listDomainTaskFiles`, `parseTasksFile`, `parseDependencies`, `readAllTasks`, `groupByWave(tasks) → Map<waveNum, Task[]>` sorted ascending, `validateNoForwardDeps(tasks)` (per wave-join-contract v1.0.0 §Between-Wave Ordering). Tasks without `**Wave**: N` default to wave 0 (backward-compat safety). Dep parser handles `NONE`/`N/A`/empty, same-domain `Task N` → `domain:TN`, and cross-domain `BLOCKED BY d3-completion-protocol Task 2` → `d3-completion-protocol:T2`. Smoke test on real M40 tree: 30 tasks across 7 domains, Wave 0=14, Wave 2=1, Wave 3=11, Wave 4=4, dep validation passes. 13/13 unit tests pass (test/m40-orchestrator-queue.test.js). Full suite: 1272/1272 (was 1259, +13). D1 Task 3 (worker lifecycle — consumes `assertCompletion` from D3-T2) next.\n- 2026-04-19 18:55: [execute] M40 Wave 0a — D1 Task 1 config loader. `bin/gsd-t-orchestrator-config.cjs` exports `loadConfig({projectDir, cliFlags, env})` with strict precedence default < `.gsd-t/orchestrator.config.json` < CLI < env (per wave-join-contract v1.0.0). Defaults: maxParallel=3, workerTimeoutMs=270000, retryOnFail=true, haltOnSecondFail=true. Rejects maxParallel > 15 (Team Mode §15 ceiling), maxParallel < 1, workerTimeoutMs < 1000, non-integer env values, corrupt config file. 11/11 unit tests pass (test/m40-orchestrator-config.test.js). Full suite: 1259/1259. D1 Tasks 2-3 (queue, worker) next.\n- 2026-04-19 18:30: [execute] M40 Wave 0a — D3 Task 1 contract freeze. `completion-signal-contract.md` v1.0.0 reviewed and frozen: 5 Done Signal conditions all testable from orchestrator side without worker cooperation, retry policy explicit (first fail → retry with \"previous attempt failed\" preamble, second fail → halt wave, timeout = FAILED retry-eligible), `assertCompletion({taskId, projectDir, expectedBranch, taskStart, skipTest, ownedPatterns})` → `{ok, missing, details}` API matches D1/D2/D6 consumers, owned patterns sourced from tasks.md (not scope.md prose) — eliminates ambiguity on \"uncommitted changes in owned scope\". Downstream D1/D2 unblocked to cite the frozen contract. D3 Task 2 (assertCompletion impl) next.\n- 2026-04-19 18:00: [milestone-planned] M40 PLANNED — 28 tasks across 7 domains. Wave 0 (foundation+gate): 15 tasks in 5 sub-groups (0a independent starts: D3-T1, D1-T1, D2-T1, D0-T1; 0b same-domain unlock; 0c cross-domain integration; 0d orchestrator CLI ready; 0e THE GATE = D0-T2 benchmark driver → D0-T3 verdict). Wave 2 (after D0 PASS): D1-T6 full worker. Wave 3 (stream feed): D4 Tasks 1-5 + D5 Tasks 1-5 + D1-T7 stream wiring. Wave 4 (recovery): D6 Tasks 1-4. REQ traceability appended to `docs/requirements.md` with 5 M40 REQs (REQ-M40-01 through REQ-M40-05), all mapped to tasks. Scope-validation: no task >5 files, no cross-domain dep >3 per task. No duplicate operations across domains (D1/D2/D3 roles are orthogonal; D4/D5 split by transport vs rendering). Tests baseline 1240/1240 pass. Ready for Wave 0 execute.\n- 2026-04-19 17:45: [milestone-partitioned] M40 PARTITIONED into 7 domains across 5 waves. D0 speed-benchmark (KILL-SWITCH GATE — Wave 0), D1 orchestrator-core, D2 task-brief-builder, D3 completion-protocol (contract-only, lands first), D4 stream-feed-server, D5 stream-feed-ui, D6 recovery-and-resume. Wave 0 assembles D3 contract + D1/D2 minimal slices + D0 benchmark run — if benchmark FAIL, milestone halts before D4/D5 ever start (per user: \"It's not worth doing if it doesn't run at least as fast[er]\"). 4 new contracts written: task-brief-contract.md v1.0.0, completion-signal-contract.md v1.0.0, stream-json-sink-contract.md v1.0.0, wave-join-contract.md v1.0.0. Existing code dispositions locked in: `bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs` INSPECT, existing events JSONL USE, `scripts/gsd-t-agent-dashboard*` (untracked, 424+1043 LOC) INSPECT-then-decide for D4/D5 promotion-or-rewrite, `bin/model-selector.js` + `bin/token-budget.cjs` NOT USED inside workers (one-shot workers don't need context meter), `commands/gsd-t-execute.md` UNCHANGED, unattended supervisor UNCHANGED. Five ambiguity-locks recorded (claude.ai-style = visual conventions not clone; streaming = replay+tail; zero-token = no LLM at all; parallelism = child_process.spawn; recovery = operator-initiated not auto). Baseline tests: 1240/1240 pass. Domains ready for `/gsd-t-plan` to fill tasks.md files.\n- 2026-04-19 11:00: [milestone-defined] M40 — External Task Orchestrator + Streaming Watcher UI committed to progress.md. Target v3.14.10 (minor bump, new major feature). Rationale: M8-sized work exceeds single-session context; in-session compaction loses cross-file reasoning; unattended is 5–10× slower with 5-min visibility gap. Solution: external node orchestrator spawns short-lived `claude -p` workers (one task per spawn = no compaction possible), pipes stream-json to a dumb local watcher UI (`localhost:7842`) that renders claude.ai-style continuous feed at zero Claude token cost. Per-wave Promise.all parallelism (default 3, max 15 per Team Mode §15) — true process-level, not subagent-level. D0 speed-benchmark gate built first: if orchestrator ≯ in-session on same domain, kill M40 before D4/D5 UI work. Seven proposed domains (D0–D6) — partition will validate/adjust. Ready for partition.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":86,"oldLines":7,"newStart":86,"newLines":7,"lines":[" "," > Prior decision log entries preserved in `.gsd-t/milestones/*/progress.md` — see archive snapshots (most recently `M40-external-task-orchestrator-2026-04-20/progress.md`) for pre-M40 history."," ","-- 2026-04-22 00:05: [resume · M43 · D1 Wave 1 · gate achieved] Unattended supervisor worker iter 1 resumed the D1 Wave 1 chain: validated the orphan-iter recovery, ran live end-to-end, marked D1-T2/T3/T4 DONE, and updated docs. **Live end-to-end validation**: `processHookPayload` invoked against a real captured Stop payload (`Stop-2026-04-21T23-24-30-274Z-a5ee3b8e-1a7.json`) referencing the live 2184-line Claude Code transcript at `~/.claude/projects/-Users-david-projects-GSD-T/a5ee3b8e-1a77-4950-ab8d-f108af026c1d.jsonl`. First fire emitted 522 rows; replay emitted 1 + skipped 521 (transcript grew by one turn between fires — proves the cursor-based idempotence works against a changing transcript). Sink `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` landed at 523 v2-schema rows, all `sessionType: \"in-session\"`, distinct `turn_id` (Claude `message.id`), parsed `inputTokens`/`outputTokens`/`cacheReadInputTokens`/`cacheCreationInputTokens`, `model: claude-opus-4-7`. **`gsd-t tokens --regenerate-log`** run against the populated sink produced 527 lines (514 data rows + 13 header/spacer) — proves D1↔D3 integration. The regen was then **reverted** via `git checkout HEAD -- .gsd-t/token-log.md` to preserve the 434-line hand-maintained file until D3-T4.1 (backfill parser extension) lands, since the transcript-sourced regen does not reproduce the historical spawn-channel rows that predate M43. **Test suite**: D1 cluster 10/10 pass; full suite 1588/1590 pass (2 pre-existing fails in `buildEventStreamEntry` and `writer_shim_safe_empty_agent_id_auto_mints_id` — same fails observed before M43 D3 landed, unrelated). **D1-T2 DONE**: `bin/gsd-t-in-session-usage.cjs` + `scripts/hooks/gsd-t-in-session-usage-hook.js` + `skipMarkdownLog` wrapper option + 10 tests (all shipped in commit `6d40e1c`). **D1-T3 DONE**: unit-integration coverage satisfies the fabricated-session requirements; live end-to-end above exceeds them. **D1-T4 DONE**: `docs/requirements.md` new \"M43 Universal Token Attribution\" section added with REQ-M43-01..06 table and D1 Branch Lock evidence block; no `bin/gsd-t.js --help` flag added because the hook install belongs in user settings.json, not the installer (documented in D1-T2). **Wave 1 gate achieved**: (1) schema v2 contract merged (D3-T1 ✓), (2) D1 branch locked (Branch B ✓), (3) first real D1 row lands in `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` — 523 real rows ✓. **Carry-forward inside M43**: D3-T4.1 (backfill parser extension to recognize pre-aggregator headless-log shapes) stays open; not a Wave 2 gate. **Next (automatic)**: supervisor advances to Wave 2 — D2 per-tool-attribution + D5 dialog-channel-meter + D6 transcript-viewer-primary-surface are parallel-safe. Team Mode spawns three subagents in the next iter.","+- 2026-04-21 16:36: [resume · M43 · D1 Wave 1 · gate achieved] Unattended supervisor worker iter 1 resumed the D1 Wave 1 chain: validated the orphan-iter recovery, ran live end-to-end, marked D1-T2/T3/T4 DONE, and updated docs. **Live end-to-end validation**: `processHookPayload` invoked against a real captured Stop payload (`Stop-2026-04-21T23-24-30-274Z-a5ee3b8e-1a7.json`) referencing the live 2184-line Claude Code transcript at `~/.claude/projects/-Users-david-projects-GSD-T/a5ee3b8e-1a77-4950-ab8d-f108af026c1d.jsonl`. First fire emitted 522 rows; replay emitted 1 + skipped 521 (transcript grew by one turn between fires — proves the cursor-based idempotence works against a changing transcript). Sink `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` landed at 523 v2-schema rows, all `sessionType: \"in-session\"`, distinct `turn_id` (Claude `message.id`), parsed `inputTokens`/`outputTokens`/`cacheReadInputTokens`/`cacheCreationInputTokens`, `model: claude-opus-4-7`. **`gsd-t tokens --regenerate-log`** run against the populated sink produced 527 lines (514 data rows + 13 header/spacer) — proves D1↔D3 integration. The regen was then **reverted** via `git checkout HEAD -- .gsd-t/token-log.md` to preserve the 434-line hand-maintained file until D3-T4.1 (backfill parser extension) lands, since the transcript-sourced regen does not reproduce the historical spawn-channel rows that predate M43. **Test suite**: D1 cluster 10/10 pass; full suite 1588/1590 pass (2 pre-existing fails in `buildEventStreamEntry` and `writer_shim_safe_empty_agent_id_auto_mints_id` — same fails observed before M43 D3 landed, unrelated). **D1-T2 DONE**: `bin/gsd-t-in-session-usage.cjs` + `scripts/hooks/gsd-t-in-session-usage-hook.js` + `skipMarkdownLog` wrapper option + 10 tests (all shipped in commit `6d40e1c`). **D1-T3 DONE**: unit-integration coverage satisfies the fabricated-session requirements; live end-to-end above exceeds them. **D1-T4 DONE**: `docs/requirements.md` new \"M43 Universal Token Attribution\" section added with REQ-M43-01..06 table and D1 Branch Lock evidence block; no `bin/gsd-t.js --help` flag added because the hook install belongs in user settings.json, not the installer (documented in D1-T2). **Wave 1 gate achieved**: (1) schema v2 contract merged (D3-T1 ✓), (2) D1 branch locked (Branch B ✓), (3) first real D1 row lands in `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` — 523 real rows ✓. **Carry-forward inside M43**: D3-T4.1 (backfill parser extension to recognize pre-aggregator headless-log shapes) stays open; not a Wave 2 gate. **Next (automatic)**: supervisor advances to Wave 2 — D2 per-tool-attribution + D5 dialog-channel-meter + D6 transcript-viewer-primary-surface are parallel-safe. Team Mode spawns three subagents in the next iter."," "," - 2026-04-21 23:55: [execute M43 · D1 Wave 1 · orphan-iter recovery] Branch B (transcript-sourced) in-session usage capture. Work was completed by an unattended worker that was SIGTERM'd mid-iteration during the 23:30 supervisor cleanup; recovered as a discrete commit since tests pass and the contract surface is sound. **`bin/gsd-t-in-session-usage.cjs`** (new) — exports `captureInSessionUsage({sessionId, transcriptPath, command, model, projectDir, sessionType, since})` and `processHookPayload({projectDir, payload})`. `captureInSessionUsage` reads the transcript JSONL at `transcriptPath`, scans for `assistant` lines with `message.usage`, generates one v2 row per turn (idempotent via `since` cursor on `message.id` / line offset), and writes through `recordSpawnRow` with `skipMarkdownLog: true` so per-turn rows land in `.gsd-t/metrics/token-usage.jsonl` only — `token-log.md` stays the regenerated view (D3 contract). Returns `{rows, reason?}`. Reasons: `missing-session-or-transcript` (graceful no-op for hook fires without payload), `no-turns` (transcript exists but has no usage-bearing assistant lines yet), `ok` (rows emitted). **`scripts/hooks/gsd-t-in-session-usage-hook.js`** (new) — thin SessionEnd / Stop hook entry point that reads the JSON payload from stdin, derives `projectDir` from `cwd`, and calls `mod.processHookPayload({projectDir, payload})`. Hook is the wire-up artifact for D1-T1's Branch B decision; no settings.json edit yet (still gated on user permission). **`bin/gsd-t-token-capture.cjs`** — added `skipMarkdownLog` boolean option to `recordSpawnRow` (default false). High-frequency producers (D1 per-turn, D2 joiner) write JSONL only; the markdown table is regenerated via `gsd-t tokens --regenerate-log`. Backward compatible: existing callers omit the flag and the `.gsd-t/token-log.md` write happens as before. **`test/m43-in-session-usage.test.js`** (new, 290 lines, 10 tests, all pass): one-turn → one row, three-turn → three rows with distinct turn_id, replay over same transcript = zero new rows (idempotence), incremental append = exactly one new row, assistant lines without usage ignored + user lines skipped, missing transcript_path → `missing-session-or-transcript`, non-existent transcript path → `no-turns` (graceful), `null` usage writes a row with `hasUsage=false`, **multi-turn emission does NOT append to token-log.md (JSONL-only)**, real-probe-shape payload (session_id + transcript_path + cwd) processes without error. **`.gsd-t/domains/m43-d1-in-session-usage-capture/tasks.md`** — task statuses updated. Files touched this iter: 4 new + 2 modified = 5 (excluding the supervisor stream-json patch in `bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs`, which is held uncommitted intentionally per session direction). D1 cluster: 10/10 pass; full suite re-run not done in this commit (will be re-run by next supervisor iter). No contract changes (v2 schema accepts the rows as-is). No new API endpoints. CLAUDE.md/README.md unchanged. Next: relaunch unattended supervisor — D1 hook payload wire-up still needs settings.json permission to fire on Stop / SessionEnd; D2/D3-T4-followup/Wave 2 next in chain."," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
